description:
&lt;p&gt;Specialist Children’s Services are a specialist health service for children and young people 0-19 years of age with mainly physical, communication, learning and developmental difficulties or disabilities, affecting their health and wellbeing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service work in partnership with children, young people, their families and carers and with other organisations. We deliver high quality, evidence based, co-ordinated and effective specialist health services to children, young people and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and forward thinking Speech and Language Therapist to lead our Preschool Service within Specialist Children&#39;s Services in a 0.5wte Band 7 position. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The postholder will participate in the planning, delivery and management of SLT services for children in mainstream schools and nurseries with moderate, severe and complex learning disabilities, and AAC needs and manage a complex and highly specialist caseload independently and advise other colleagues, this includes assessment, diagnosis, development and implementation of highly specialist SLT treatment.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lucy Kassell, Clinical Lead Speech and Language Therapist. Email: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;lucy.kassell1@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Phone: 07827 233 615.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
